						               													<description>The box contains a total of 32 cards, namely:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     24 warrior cards&amp;#10;     4 joker cards (one for each symbol/strength)&amp;#10;     4 rule cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Playmobil Dragon Fight players play cards to win tricks.  Unlike other trump card games, this game uses four different suits, from which the player can choose to play their card for.  Every card has four symbols/strengths, these are: Tactic, Attack, Defense and Range.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game, the warrior cards are shuffled and all are dealt among the players as equally as possible.  Every player gets one joker card, the remaining joker cards are removed from the game.  After receiving their cards, players put them -face down- in front of them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The starting player takes the top card from his deck and pick one of the four symbols to play.  They call out both the symbol and the point value.  Then the other players take the top card of their decks and call out the point value for the chosen symbol and show their cards to prove their claims.  The player with the highest point value in the chosen strength wins the trick and places all cards -face down- at the bottom of their stack.  The game continues until a single player owns all the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Jokers can be used to win a trick, they always have the highest point value.  But they can only be played at beginning of the turn or if the corresponding symbol has been called out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;user summary&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
